@NODE "INFO" "Introduction and function summary"
@PREV "MAIN"
@TOC "MAIN"



          @{"  GUI of RecoverDelDir  " LINK "/Illustration/RecoverDeldir.png/main"}  RecoverDelDir.png




          @{b}RecoverDelDir.dopus5@{ub}
          recovers deleted Files from partitions using
           - Ami File Safe
           - Professional File System II
           - SmartFileSystem
          and copies these files to the directory which is being displayed
          in the file lister you started the program from, using RAM: as a
          temporary directory.

          The suffixes ($AAA or @000) will be removed and the files' protection bits
          will be restored.

          There is no need to specify a destination lister.
          If you specify a destination which is different from the source,
          an appropiate destination lister will be opened automatically.

          Before the list showing the deleted files is set up, RecoverDelDir will also
          scan each deleted file to see if it fits a DOpus filetype description.
          If it does, the DOpus filetype will also be displayed in the list.


@endnode
@NODE "REQUIRE" "What you need to use RecoverDelDir.dopus5"

      @{fg shine}_____________________________________________________________________@{fg text}
     @{fg shine}|@{fg text}                                                                     |
     @{fg shine}|@{fg text}                      @{fg shine}@{b}I M P O R T A N T  ! ! !@{ub}@{fg text}                       |
     @{fg shine}|@{fg text}_____________________________________________________________________|


     @{b}To use many of the hyperlinks in this document, you need the following:@{ub}

     @{b}Rexxmast@{ub} running
     If @{" this gadget " rx "/ARexx/Check Sys:System/Rexxmast Port REXX"} doesn't do anything, RexxMast probaly isn't running.
     Run @{" SYS:System/RexxMast " SYSTEM "SYS:System/RexxMast"} to invoce REXXMast.

     A @{fg shine}@{b}running@{ub}@{fg text} @{b}Directory Opus 5.5@{ub}    @{" Test " rx "/ARexx/Check DOpus5:DirectoryOpus Port DOPUS.1"}

     The files Check, Lister and SystemReq from the AREXX-directory of
     this package.

     If you simply @{b}unpack@{ub} the package and leave everything as it is and
     view this guide from within the resulting directories, the guide
     should find everything it needs. :-)

     _________________________________________________________________________@{fg shine}
     -------------------------------------------------------------------------@{fg text}

     @{b}To use RecoverDelDir, you need to have the following things:@{ub}

     A working @{FG shine}@{b}Amiga@{ub}@{FG text} (what a surprise :-) )
     @{b}Workbench 3.1@{ub}  (or so I suspect)
     A partition which is formatted under AFS, PFS2 or SFS

     A fully @{" set up " rx "/ARexx/Check DOpus5:DirectoryOpus 5.5"} and @{" functionable " rx "/ARexx/Check DOpus5:DirectoryOpus Port DOPUS.1"} @{b}Directory Opus 5.5,@{ub} preferably running as
       WB-replacement with "Use WB" set in the screenmode configuration window.
       To by able to start RDD by doubleclicking its icons, you will need at least
       DirOpus @{" Magellan " rx "/ARexx/Check DOpus5:DirectoryOpus 5.6"} (I). .

     @{b}RexxMast@{ub} running
       If @{" this gadget " rx "/ARexx/Check Sys:System/Rexxmast Port REXX"} doesn't do anything, REXXMast is probably not running.
       Simply run @{" SYS:System/RexxMast " SYSTEM "SYS:System/RexxMast"} to invoke it temporaly.
       Is it @{" active " rx "/ARexx/Check Sys:System/Rexxmast Port REXX"} at last ?

     @{b}Setting up Rexxmast for permanent use@{ub}
       If neither your @{" startup-sequence " link "SYS:s/Startup-Sequence/main"} nor your @{" user-Startup " link "SYS:s/user-startup/main"}
       contains a command line like @{FG SHINE}@{b}SYS:System/Rexxmast >NIL:@{ub}@{FG TEXT},
       please insert this very line into the file @{" s:user-startup " SYSTEM "ED s:User-startup"},
       thus starting Rexxmast at every bootup.

     @{b}tritonrexx.library@{ub}      by Juergen Kohrmeyer                           @{" Check " rx "/ARexx/Check Libs:tritonrexx.library"}
       Aminet ( 9) - util/rexx/TritonRexx376.lha
       Aminet(10) - util/rexx/TRX_Tools.lha
